      • Pump

        public Pump(@NotNull
            @NotNull Pump pump)
        Create a pump with same values that the pump received. This is a shallow copy, i.e., If the field value is a reference to an object (e.g., a memory address) it copies the reference. If it is necessary for the object to be completely independent of the original you must ensure that you replace the reference to the contained objects.

        You must replace node1 and node2 to do the copy independent of the original

        Parameters:
        pump - the pump to copy
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if pump is null

    • Method Detail

      • getProperty

        public java.lang.Object getProperty(Pump.PumpProperty key)
        Get the property by key.

        When key is Pump.PumpProperty.HEAD value has to be the id of the Curve has a String

        When key is Pump.PumpProperty.PATTERN value has to be the id of a Pattern has a String

        When key is Pump.PumpProperty.SPEED value has to be Double

        When key is Pump.PumpProperty.POWER value has to be Double

        When key is null so the property isn't setting up
        Parameters:
        key - the key of property
        Returns:
        value the value (Double, Curve or Pattern or null)

      • setProperty

        public void setProperty(@NotNull
                        @NotNull Pump.PumpProperty key,
                        java.lang.Object value)
        Set the property.

        When key is Pump.PumpProperty.HEAD value has to be the id of the Curve has a String

        When key is Pump.PumpProperty.PATTERN value has to be the id of a Pattern has a String

        When key is Pump.PumpProperty.SPEED value has to be Double

        When key is Pump.PumpProperty.POWER value has to be Double

        Pump.PumpProperty.POWER and Pump.PumpProperty.HEAD cannot be configured at the same time. The last addition is the one that remains.

        Parameters:
        key - the key
        value - the value (Double, Curve or Pattern)
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if value type is not valid to key used.
